is so, so simple.

15
00:00:50,720 --> 00:00:54,640
You just forget about subjects like I or
you for a second.

16
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:58,680
All you have to do is start your sentence
with the main action word, the verb, in

17
00:00:58,680 --> 00:01:02,840
its basic original form, like the form
you'd find in a dictionary.

18
00:01:02,840 --> 00:01:08,400
No ing, no s's at the end, nothing extra.
Just the verb itself.

19
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:11,640
And check this out. This one simple rule
works for everything.

20
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:16,160
For regular action verbs, what you might
call a ipandoshi, it's just, come here.

21
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:20,520
Or stand up. Easy. But what about the
b-verb? Or b-doshi?

22
00:01:20,520 --> 00:01:23,800
Well, you don't use am, is, or are. Nope.

23
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:28,040
You just use its original base form, b. So
you get, be quiet.

24
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:33,140
Be careful. See? Super simple, right?
Alright, time for a quick quiz.

25
00:01:33,140 --> 00:01:34,660
