up.

79
00:05:06,060 --> 00:05:07,740
Now think about it for a second.

80
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:12,740
what part of a normal English sentence
seems to be missing.

81
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:16,180
I'm sure your English teacher has told you
this a million times.

82
00:05:16,180 --> 00:05:19,640
Every English sentence needs a subject and
a verb, right?

83
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:22,580
Like I study or she plays tennis.

84
00:05:22,580 --> 00:05:25,860
But in stand up, we've only got the verb
stand.

85
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:31,060
So where in the world is the subject? And
here it is, the big reveal,

86
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:36,020
the secret subject is you. That's right,
the subject is there,

87
00:05:36,020 --> 00:05:39,520
but it's invisible. In every single
command sentence,

88
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:44,200
the subject is always automatically the
person you're talking to, you.

89
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,960
So when you say stand up,

90
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:51,040
what your brain is really saying is you
stand up. Kinda cool, right?

91
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:55,620
And that is what makes these sentences so
powerful and so special.

92
00:05:55,620 --> 00:05:57,380
They don't even need to say the word you

93
00:05:57,380 --> 00:06:01,320
because it's already built right in. This
makes commands the fastest,

94
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:03,400
most direct way to communicate with
someone.

95
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:06,480
It's like a direct line to the person
you're talking to.

96
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:09,520
So there you have it. Your command power-
up is complete.

